  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nUpdate the design of the warning users see when they try to use the Wallet Send function to send tokens directly to a smart contract.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user without technical knowledge, I want to be warned when I am about to make a common mistake, such ash sending tokens directly to whatever I think is the right place.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n![sending_funds_to_smart_contract_warning](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22846356/93913718-5f0f8700-fcfd-11ea-9015-a98efbe57666.png)\r\n\r\nTitle: Warning!\r\n\r\nDescription: This address is a smart contract, funds sent to this address may be lost. Use Status DApp Browser to interact with Dapps.\r\n\r\nActions: [Cancel] <-- primary       [Send funds to this address] <-- secondary\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nVisual design of this warning is updated to match the attached mock\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nThis is a follow on to issue #11136\r\n\r\nThis should be tackled at the same time as issue #11210\r\n",
